Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2},
separating whites from greens. Mince @dill{1/4%ounce}. Dice @tomato{1}
into 1/2-inch pieces. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta
cooking water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add garlic, scallion whites, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant and slightly
softened, ~{1%minute}.

Reduce heat to medium; stir in @veggie stock concentrate{2}, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon},
half the dill, half the @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and 1/3 cup pasta cooking
water (1/2 cup for 4 servings). (Ladle straight from the pot if pasta
hasn't finished cooking yet.) Cook, stirring and smashing feta with the
back of a #spoon{} or #spatula{}, until sauce is creamy and thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in tomato and @spinach{5%ounce} (add in batches if necessary). Cook,
stirring, until tomato is softened and spinach is wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Taste and season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

To pan with sauce, stir in spaghetti, a drizzle of olive oil, a squeeze of
lemon juice, and as much remaining dill as you like; toss until thoroughly
coated.

> If needed, add another drizzle of olive oil and reserved pasta cooking water
> a splash at a time until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}; top with scallion greens and remaining feta.
Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.